Source: ulak
Section: database
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Ruohang Feng <rh@vonng.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), postgresql-all (>= 217~), libcurl4-openssl-dev (>= 7), libssl-dev
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Rules-Requires-Root: no
Homepage: https://github.com/zeybek/ulak

Package: postgresql-PGVERSION-ulak
Architecture: any
Provides: postgresql-ulak
Depends: ${postgresql:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Transactional outbox and asynchronous delivery extension for PostgreSQL
  ulak implements the transactional outbox pattern inside PostgreSQL, storing
  outbound events atomically with business data and dispatching them
  asynchronously from background workers.
  This package builds the default core and HTTP delivery support.
